ENTRY       EC 1.5.99.4                 Enzyme
NAME        nicotine dehydrogenase;
            nicotine oxidase;
            D-nicotine oxidase;
            nicotine:(acceptor) 6-oxidoreductase (hydroxylating);
            L-nicotine oxidase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-NH group of donors;
            With other acceptors
SYSNAME     nicotine:acceptor 6-oxidoreductase (hydroxylating)
REACTION    (S)-nicotine + acceptor + H2O = (S)-6-hydroxynicotine + reduced acceptor [RN:R02860]
ALL_REAC    R02860 > R07946
SUBSTRATE   (S)-nicotine [CPD:C00745];
            acceptor [CPD:C00028];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     (S)-6-hydroxynicotine [CPD:C01056];
            reduced acceptor [CPD:C00030]
COMMENT     A metalloprotein (FMN). The enzyme can act on both the naturally found (S)-enantiomer and the synthetic (R)-enantiomer of nicotine, with retention of configuration in both cases [4].
